I see this pattern sometimes attempted but it's incorrect:

```javascript
webpack: (config, { isServer }) => {
    if (isServer) {
      config.resolve = config.resolve || {};
      config.resolve.fallback = {
        ...config.resolve.fallback,
        crypto: false,
        net: false,
      };
    }
    return config;
  },
```

This won't work because: Setting resolve.fallback to false silences the build error but makes the modules undefined at runtime, causing crashes when the code actually runs.

